# data
trial1 <- c(45, 24, 97, 254)
trial2 <- c(106, 41, 107, 166)
trial3 <- c(243, 64, 65, 48)

# model
model_text <- "
# Multinomial Processing Tree
model{
  # MPT Category Probabilities for Word Pairs
  theta[1] <- c * r
  theta[2] <- (1-c) * pow(u,2)
  theta[3] <- (1-c) * 2 * u * (1-u)
  theta[4] <- c * (1-r) + (1-c) * pow(1-u,2)
  # Data       
  k[1:4] ~ dmulti(theta[1:4],n)
  # Priors
  c ~ dbeta(1,1)
  r ~ dbeta(1,1)
  u ~ dbeta(1,1)
}
"

parameters = c("c", "r", "u")
data <- list("k", "n")

# Trial 1
k <- trial1
n <- sum(k)
samples1 = jags(data, parameters.to.save = parameters,
               model.file = textConnection(model_text), 
               n.chains=2, n.iter=20000, n.burnin=2000, n.thin=3)

# https://mjskay.github.io/ggdist/articles/slabinterval.html
f1 <- bind_rows(p1, p2, p3) %>% 
  ggplot(aes(fill = trial, color = trial, x = c)) +
  stat_slab(alpha = .3) +
  stat_pointinterval(position = position_dodge(width = .4, preserve = "single")) +
  labs(
    y = "Probability Density"
  ) +
  scale_y_continuous(breaks = NULL) +
  theme_bw()

f2 <- bind_rows(p1, p2, p3) %>%

#    u  
meanU <- bind_rows(p1, p2, p3) %>% 
  group_by(trial) %>% 
  summarise(uM = mean(u)) %>% 
  ungroup()
uConst <- meanU$uM

# model: u prior
